1. Deploy this construct from blueprint (You've done this already.)

2. Right-click the programming board and select 'Advanced' --> 'Copy Lua configuration to clipboard'

3. Place a new programming board on the target construct you want to add Equinox OS to

4. Right-click the programming board and select 'Advanced' --> 'Paste Lua configuration from clipboard'

5. Right-click the programming board and select 'Advanced' --> 'Edit Lua parameters'. Change the values to your specifications

*** For "totalDryMass" use the build helper. Add the values shown for honeycomb mass and element mass together to calculate your "totalDryMass".

*** For "cargoLiftMax" enter the max amount in tons that your ship can carry before becoming overweight.

6. Connect the core, hub, and minimum of one screen to the programming board
